5. Technical Stack

Python: Primary language for backend logic and data processing

Frameworks & Libraries
• Kivy: Cross-platform Python framework for TV interface development
• Flask: Lightweight web framework for API development and data management (NIX)
• Pillow: Image processing for photo management and QR code reading
• Requests: HTTP library for external API integrations

Database
• SQLite: Lightweight database for local data storage (medications, contacts, appointments)
• JSON Files: Simple data storage for configuration and user preferences

AI Models or Integrations
• OpenAI API: Natural language processing for voice commands and text-to-speech
• QR Code Libraries: Python QR code generation and reading capabilities
• Calendar APIs: Google and iOS Calendar integration

Deployment & Hosting
• Raspberry Pi: Local deployment on TV-connected device for reliability and privacy
• Local Network: System operates on home network to ensure data privacy
• Cloud Backup: Optional cloud backup for emergency contact information

Technology Justification
• Kivy: Chosen for its ability to create large, touch-friendly interfaces suitable for TV displays
• Python: Selected for rapid development and extensive library support for healthcare applications
• SQLite: Ideal for local data storage with minimal setup requirements
• Raspberry Pi: Cost-effective, reliable platform that can be easily integrated with existing TV systems

Security and Privacy
• Data Protection: maintain HIPAA-aligned privacy standards

Summary of Expected Impact

The Dementia Care Digital Assistant aims to reduce caregiver stress and patient confusion by providing a dementia-friendly interface that integrates time orientation, medication safety, and emergency preparedness. By consolidating tools into a single accessible system, this delivers a realistic solution for families navigating dementia. The success will be measured through task completion rates, caregiver satisfaction, and theoretical reduced emergency time and confusion, supporting the independence and safety of patients and alleviating burden on families.

